[1
Date: 18 Oct 2001
From: ProMED-mail
Source: Agencia EFE, 18 Oct 2001 [edited

Kenya family is the first victim of bioterrorism outside U.S
------------------------------------------------------------
Four members of a Kenyan family have tested positive for anthrax after
receiving a letter from the United States, making them the first victims of
bioterrorism outside the United States, Kenya's Public Health Minister Sam
Ongeri said Thursday. The family received a letter postmarked in the United
States containing a white powdery substance 3 days before the 11 Sep 2001
attacks on New York and Washington, Ongeri said in a press conference.
Two other letters, postmarked in Pakistan and addressed to the United
Nations center in Nairobi, are being examined for the presence of the
deadly bacteria by officials, the minister added.
The announcement was made the day after representatives from 30 African
countries met in Dakar, Senegal, and failed to sign an anti-terrorist
agreement that would help prevent the continent from becoming a stage for
attacks or serving as a base for extremist groups.
