[2
Date: 18 Oct 2001
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Reuters Online, 18 Oct 2001 [edited

Health Minister Confirms Anthrax Case in Kenya
----------------------------------------------
Kenyan Health minister Sam Ongeri said on Thursday that a letter sent to an
unidentified Kenyan businessman in Nyeri, about 70 miles north of the
capital Nairobi, had tested positive for the anthrax bacteria. "On 17 Oct
2001 3 suspected cases (of anthrax) were reported to the ministry," Ongeri
told a news conference in the Kenyan capital Nairobi. "One of the samples
tested positive by stain and smear."
He said the letter was posted from Atlanta, United States, and passed via
Miami.
Two other suspect letters were undergoing tests in Kenya, he said, one of
which was delivered to the United Nations in Nairobi on Wednesday.
